The paper discusses the problem of monocular depth estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions scene reconstruction and object recognition, which are related to robotics (cs.RO). The techniques used in the papers reviewed include supervised, weakly-supervised, and unsupervised learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the difficulty of accurately estimating depth in scenes with rich geometric detailing, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
